                translation: "The ancient masters of the Tao didn't try to make people clever, but rather helped them stay simple. People become hard to govern when they have too much cunning; so governing a state through cleverness harms it, while governing without cleverness blesses it. Knowing this distinction is itself a kind of model to follow, and holding to that model consistently is called mysterious virtue, deep, far-reaching, seemingly the reverse of ordinary ways, yet ultimately leading to great harmony.",
                theme: "wuwei",
