                translation: "Boldness that dares to act recklessly leads to death; boldness that dares to hold back leads to life. Of these two, one benefits and one harms, but who really knows heaven's reasoning? Even the sage finds this puzzling. The way of heaven doesn't strive, yet it wins; doesn't speak, yet it responds; isn't summoned, yet it arrives; moves slowly, yet plans well. Heaven's net is vast, its mesh wide, yet nothing slips through it.",
                theme: "nature",
